## 📦 **MANDATORY: Container Infrastructure Rules** ✅ **ENFORCED**

**🚨 CRITICAL: PODMAN + KIND ONLY - ZERO TOLERANCE POLICY**

**🤖 NOTE: All Mix commands are now automatically enforced through `Intelitor.ContainerCompliance` - developers just use normal Mix commands and get automatic container execution with PHICS hot-reloading.**

### **Container Technology Restrictions**

**✅ PERMITTED:**
1.0 - **Podman 5.4.1** - Rootless container runtime via DevEnv/Nix ONLY
2.0 - **Kind (Kubernetes in Docker)** - Kubernetes testing and development
3.0 - **DevEnv/Nix integration** - Seamless container image building and deployment
4.0 - **NixOS Container Registry ONLY** - registry.nixos.org/nixos/ images exclusively

**❌ ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN:**
1.0 - **LXC/LXD** - BANNED - No system containers, no privileged containers  
2.0 - **Docker daemon** - BANNED - Use Podman for all container operations
3.0 - **Docker run commands** - BANNED - Use `podman run` instead of `docker run`
4.0 - **Docker CLI** - BANNED - No `docker` commands allowed under any condition
5.0 - **docker.io registry** - BANNED - Use registry.nixos.org/nixos/ ONLY
6.0 - **Docker Hub images** - BANNED - NixOS container images exclusively
7.0 - **Containerd** - BANNED - Podman provides all required functionality
8.0 - **systemd-nspawn** - BANNED - No alternative container runtimes
9.0 - **Any non-Podman/Kind solution** - BANNED - Zero exceptions

### **Container Enforcement Rules (ZERO TOLERANCE)**

**🚫 PROHIBITED COMMANDS:**
```bash
# ❌ FORBIDDEN - ANY LXC/LXD usage
lxc list/exec/start/stop/launch    # VIOLATION: Use podman equivalents

# ❌ FORBIDDEN - Docker CLI usage (ZERO TOLERANCE)
docker run/exec/ps/start/stop      # VIOLATION: Use podman equivalents
docker pull/push/build             # VIOLATION: Use podman equivalents  
systemctl start docker            # VIOLATION: No Docker daemon allowed
docker-compose                    # VIOLATION: Use podman-compose

# ❌ FORBIDDEN - Docker registry usage (ZERO TOLERANCE)
docker.io/library/postgres        # VIOLATION: Use registry.nixos.org/nixos/postgresql:17
docker.io/library/redis           # VIOLATION: Use registry.nixos.org/nixos/redis:7
docker.io/prom/prometheus          # VIOLATION: Use registry.nixos.org/nixos/prometheus:latest
docker.io/grafana/grafana          # VIOLATION: Use registry.nixos.org/nixos/grafana:latest
```

**✅ REQUIRED COMMANDS:**
```bash
# ✅ CORRECT - LOCAL REGISTRY DEFAULT (MANDATORY - NO CHANGES WITHOUT FORMAL APPROVAL)
podman run --name app localhost/intelitor-app:nixos-devenv          # Application containers (DEFAULT)
podman run --name db localhost/intelitor-postgres:nixos-devenv      # Database containers (DEFAULT)
podman exec app command                                              # Container command execution
podman ps -a                                                         # Container status checking

# ✅ FALLBACK - NixOS registry (only if local registry unavailable)
podman run -d --name db registry.nixos.org/nixos/postgresql:17       # Database containers (FALLBACK)
podman run -d --name cache registry.nixos.org/nixos/redis:7          # Cache containers (FALLBACK)
podman run -d --name web registry.nixos.org/nixos/nginx:latest       # Web server containers (FALLBACK)

# ✅ CORRECT - Kind Kubernetes operations  
kind create cluster --name intelitor   # Kubernetes cluster creation
kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml       # Kubernetes deployments
```

### **Daily Container Development Workflow**

```bash
# Enter development environment with Podman + Kind
devenv shell

# Container management via Elixir scripts ONLY
elixir scripts/performance/podman_direct_manager.exs --status
elixir scripts/performance/podman_final_setup.exs --complete
elixir scripts/performance/setup_kind_kubernetes.exs --deploy

# Development workflow via containers (UNIFIED ARCHITECTURE)
podman exec intelitor-app mix compile --dashboard --strategy smart
podman exec intelitor-app mix test --coverage --gold
kubectl apply -f k8s/development.yaml
```

