5.0 - **Use Mix for everything** - Tasks, tests, quality checks
6.0 - **Zero tolerance for warnings** - All must be fixed
7.0 - **Test everything** - Minimum 95% coverage with comprehensive strategies
8.0 - **Follow Ash patterns** - Use framework capabilities
9.0 - **Maintain tenant isolation** - Security is paramount
10.0 - **Document changes** - Keep docs synchronized
11.0 - **Use devenv.sh** - No alternative package managers
12.0 - **🚨 MANDATORY: Claude AI compilation mode** - ALL compilation through `mix claude compilation` (NEW DEFAULT)
13.0 - **🆕 Parallel domain compilation** - Use `mix claude compilation --parallel-domains` for maximum efficiency
14.0 - **🆕 Claude AI workflow integration** - Use `--claude-mode` flags for all scripts and operations
15.0 - **🚨 FORBIDDEN: Direct mix commands** - Never use `mix compile`, `mix test`, or `mix dialyzer` directly
16.0 - **🕒 MANDATORY: Timestamp validation** - ALL files must have current timestamps (July 2025), run daily audits
17.0 - **🚨 ZERO TOLERANCE: Historical timestamps** - No 2025-01 through 2025-06 dates allowed, immediate correction required
18.0 - **📋 PRE-COMMIT: Timestamp checks** - Mandatory timestamp validation before all commits using validation tools
19.0 - **🤖 CLAUDE TIMESTAMP RULE** - Claude MUST always use `$(date)` command or equivalent to get CURRENT system time, NEVER use assumed/cached timestamps

